<heading>mem - Show runtime memory usage.</heading>

<rule/>

<heading level="2">
Usage
</heading>
<pre>
  mem
</pre>

<heading level="2">
Description
</heading>

<paragraph>
Displays the current memory footprint of the runtime process (RSS, Virtual)
together with overall system memory availability.
</paragraph>
<paragraph>
This is the first stage of a diagnostics command that will be extended
with per-bundle and per-executor memory tracking.
</paragraph>

<heading level="2">
See also
</heading>

<paragraph>
<code>health</code> — validate node structure.
</paragraph>
